L4 - Unmanaged 'long' type is 4 bytes long (Win32, Win64 and Unix32)
L8 - Unmanaged 'long' type is 8 bytes long (Unix64)
P0 - Unmanaged structs are packed with the platform default byte alignment (Unix32 and Unix64)
P1 - Unmanaged structs are packed with 1-byte alignment (Win32 and Win64)
